      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MR OREO (5) recorded a gutsy maiden victory last time out over 1250m at Cairns, scoring by a nose. Looks well placed and he can go on with it. PROPERLEIGH (9) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1000m at Home Hill, beaten 13 lengths into seventh. Finds a nice race and can feature in the finish. COPPABELLA ROAD (1) finished 2.75 lengths away in fifth last time out over 950m at Cairns two-and-a-half weeks ago as $3.5 favourite. Tackles a longer journey this time. Has good early toe so he should be handy in the run. Should be involved in the finish. SHEZA CHIQUITITA (4) turned in another moderate effort last start when 5.5 lengths from the winner in sixth over 1250m at Cairns. Better than recent efforts suggest.",
